WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:00.084 --> 00:00:02.086
Can we please discuss
how epic it is you have

2
00:00:02.169 --> 00:00:03.379
a genuine Seattle prospect?

3
00:00:03.462 --> 00:00:04.755
Previously on Elle...

4
00:00:04.839 --> 00:00:06.382
He's not a prospect. Madison.

5
00:00:06.465 --> 00:00:07.967
Miles is with Shannon.

6
00:00:08.050 --> 00:00:10.594
and Shannon's basically
the coolest senior at Rainier West.

7
00:00:10.678 --> 00:00:11.887
I just need to move back to L.A.

8
00:00:11.971 --> 00:00:13.723
and get myself out of this mess.

9
00:00:15.349 --> 00:00:17.393
I could kiss a zillion guys.

10
00:00:17.476 --> 00:00:20.020
you do not write S-L-U-T

11
00:00:20.104 --> 00:00:21.689
-on someone's locker.
-[Kimberly] Hmm. what if

12
00:00:21.772 --> 00:00:23.733
the S-L-U-T is swooning

13
00:00:23.816 --> 00:00:26.444
over her wannabe bestie's B-O-Y?

14
00:00:26.527 --> 00:00:27.903
Get a boyfriend who isn't

15
00:00:27.987 --> 00:00:30.406
Miles and throw Kimberly off the scent.

16
00:00:30.489 --> 00:00:31.741
[Dustin] I just need you

17
00:00:31.824 --> 00:00:32.658
to get one of your parents

18
00:00:32.742 --> 00:00:34.368
to go to the school board meeting tonight.

19
00:00:34.452 --> 00:00:37.079
snag one of the school budgets.

20
00:00:37.163 --> 00:00:40.332
As previously discussed.
the contents of this stays between us

21
00:00:40.416 --> 00:00:42.042
till we commit to a plan.

22
00:00:43.252 --> 00:00:46.464
-What the hell. Elle-A?
-You lied to me!

23
00:00:46.547 --> 00:00:49.258
And I'm not trying to get in your way.
but this isn't about me.

24
00:00:49.341 --> 00:00:50.760
[Liz] It's about me.

25
00:00:52.011 --> 00:00:53.137
Elle's trying to protect me.

26
00:00:53.220 --> 00:00:54.680
Duh.

27
00:00:54.764 --> 00:00:57.475
Uh. Chad and Charlie
live with their son down the street.

28
00:00:57.558 --> 00:00:58.768
Oh. that's nice.

29
00:00:58.851 --> 00:01:00.019
[Miles] Hey.

30
00:01:02.646 --> 00:01:03.939
Hi.

31
00:01:04.023 --> 00:01:07.151
Guess it's gonna be harder
to avoid me now. though.

32
00:01:07.234 --> 00:01:08.360
[scoffs]

33
00:01:10.613 --> 00:01:12.615
[bright music playing]

34
00:01:18.287 --> 00:01:21.207
-Ooh!
-[sighs]

35
00:01:23.000 --> 00:01:24.835
That was so necessary.

36
00:01:24.919 --> 00:01:27.421
Can't believe we haven't done
mother-daughter manis since we got here.

37
00:01:27.505 --> 00:01:29.548
Like water in the desert.

38
00:01:31.008 --> 00:01:33.636
Do you know where
the nail polish remover is?

39
00:01:33.719 --> 00:01:35.471
Oh. You're taking it off?

40
00:01:35.554 --> 00:01:37.097
I thought we liked "moody mauve."

41
00:01:37.181 --> 00:01:40.184
Well. that's because our other options
were "gunmetal" and "corpse."

42
00:01:42.645 --> 00:01:45.189
[Eileen] Hi. this is a message
for Elle Woods.

43
00:01:45.272 --> 00:01:47.775
This is Eileen from
Cosmopolitan magazine.

44
00:01:47.858 --> 00:01:49.401
I'm thrilled to tell you
that you're a finalist

45
00:01:49.485 --> 00:01:52.947
in the Cosmopolitan
Fun Fearless Female L.A.

46
00:01:53.030 --> 00:01:53.989
internship program.

47
00:01:54.073 --> 00:01:54.990
-What is she talking about?
-All of our FFF finalists

48
00:01:55.074 --> 00:01:56.700
submit five-minute videos

49
00:01:56.784 --> 00:02:00.496
describing how they're a fun.
fearless female at home. at school

50
00:02:00.579 --> 00:02:02.790
and in their community.
We look forward to your application.

51
00:02:02.873 --> 00:02:05.167
-[machine beeps]
-Elle. what was that about?

52
00:02:06.335 --> 00:02:07.795
Oh. that? Right.

53
00:02:07.878 --> 00:02:09.296
That seems to be

54
00:02:09.380 --> 00:02:12.508
a message about a small.
trivial contest I applied to.

55
00:02:12.591 --> 00:02:15.219
Just on a lark. You know me and larks.

56
00:02:15.302 --> 00:02:16.846
She said it's an internship.

57
00:02:17.555 --> 00:02:18.597
Did she?

58
00:02:18.681 --> 00:02:20.182
In L.A.

59
00:02:21.559 --> 00:02:23.519
See. I'd forgotten that detail.

60
00:02:23.602 --> 00:02:27.273
It would require me to live in L.A.
next semester if I won.

61
00:02:27.356 --> 00:02:29.233
Which I won't.

62
00:02:29.316 --> 00:02:32.319
Well. if this happens.
I-I mean. you'd need

63
00:02:32.403 --> 00:02:35.447
a chaperone.
I'd have to go back to L.A. with you.

64
00:02:35.531 --> 00:02:39.451
meaning I'd step away
from my social and charitable endeavors.

65
00:02:40.327 --> 00:02:43.539
But if it's really important to you.
I'll do it.

66
00:02:47.710 --> 00:02:50.796
I think it could possibly
be the best thing ever?

67
00:02:51.881 --> 00:02:53.299
Of course it could be.

68
00:02:53.382 --> 00:02:54.383
Oh. thank God.

69
00:02:54.466 --> 00:02:56.719
-[squeals]
-Yeah. this is huge!

70
00:02:56.802 --> 00:02:58.929
And if you want a career in fashion.

71
00:02:59.013 --> 00:03:00.848
you have to be in L.A.

72
00:03:00.931 --> 00:03:04.560
Or New York. but New York
isn't really for us Woods girls.

73
00:03:04.643 --> 00:03:07.980
It's more for... women with lowlights.

74
00:03:08.063 --> 00:03:09.815
Mm.

75
00:03:09.899 --> 00:03:12.902
So. for the video submission.
okay. we have to

76
00:03:12.985 --> 00:03:14.862
straddle that line between

77
00:03:14.945 --> 00:03:18.282
prestigious enough
to be nominated for an Oscar

78
00:03:18.365 --> 00:03:20.034
but not pretentious enough to win.

79
00:03:20.117 --> 00:03:21.535
I'm thinking black and white.

80
00:03:21.619 --> 00:03:22.620
Like Madonna in Truth or Dare.

81
00:03:22.703 --> 00:03:24.872
-Yes. exactly.
-Uh-oh.

82
00:03:24.955 --> 00:03:27.499
Sounds like the Woods women
are up to something.

83
00:03:27.583 --> 00:03:30.210
Honey. Elle won a spring internship

84
00:03:30.294 --> 00:03:32.379
at Cosmopolitan magazine

85
00:03:32.463 --> 00:03:34.632
-in Century City.
-I didn't win. I'm a finalist.

86
00:03:34.715 --> 00:03:36.133
Century City as in L.A.?

87
00:03:36.216 --> 00:03:37.051
Mm-hmm.

88
00:03:37.134 --> 00:03:39.762
Wow. How are we gonna make that work?
We live here now.

89
00:03:39.845 --> 00:03:42.097
Well. I offered to chaperone.

90
00:03:42.181 --> 00:03:44.350
And there's still
a million details to iron out.

91
00:03:44.433 --> 00:03:45.392
Like winning.

92
00:03:45.476 --> 00:03:48.479
So we need to make a mood board. Stat.

93
00:03:48.562 --> 00:03:51.690
I want to think of these two words
as our guiding light.

94
00:03:51.774 --> 00:03:54.401
Authentic and curated.

95
00:03:54.485 --> 00:03:55.527
Yeah. love it.

96
00:03:55.611 --> 00:03:56.737
I have to fly out my nail girl.

97
00:03:56.820 --> 00:03:58.530
'cause there's no way
you're winning this thing

98
00:03:58.614 --> 00:04:00.783
with these baby coffins on your nails.

99
00:04:00.866 --> 00:04:03.077
So. all I have to do
is make a groundbreaking video.

100
00:04:03.160 --> 00:04:05.621
which. obviously. I have in the bag.

101
00:04:05.704 --> 00:04:07.456
You think Scorsese
would be right for this?

102
00:04:07.539 --> 00:04:09.083
Potentially not. We're thinking

103
00:04:09.166 --> 00:04:10.751
more of a Truth or Dare aesthetic.

104
00:04:10.834 --> 00:04:12.378
But the problem with black and white is...

105
00:04:12.461 --> 00:04:14.630
-There's no pink.
-Exactly.

106
00:04:14.713 --> 00:04:17.174
So. I need a new take. ASAP or sooner.

107
00:04:17.257 --> 00:04:19.009
Speaking of...

108
00:04:19.093 --> 00:04:20.719
well. nothing.

109
00:04:20.803 --> 00:04:22.471
I was gonna talk to you
about it when I visited.

110
00:04:22.554 --> 00:04:24.974
but you know I could never
keep anything from you.

111
00:04:25.057 --> 00:04:27.142
Oh. my God. What is it?

112
00:04:27.226 --> 00:04:30.020
Okay. you can just rip the Band-Aid off.
I can take it.

113
00:04:30.104 --> 00:04:32.022
It's about homecoming.

114
00:04:32.106 --> 00:04:33.983
I need you to know
that I put up a valiant fight.

115
00:04:34.066 --> 00:04:35.651
I did everything that you suggested.

116
00:04:35.734 --> 00:04:37.194
I canvassed. I phone banked.

117
00:04:37.277 --> 00:04:38.320
I flirted heavily

118
00:04:38.404 --> 00:04:40.698
across all categories. But nobody

119
00:04:40.781 --> 00:04:42.700
knew what "in absentia" meant.

120
00:04:43.701 --> 00:04:46.704
I'm sorry. Elle. but you're not
on the homecoming court.

121
00:04:46.787 --> 00:04:47.997
What?

122
00:04:48.080 --> 00:04:49.832
Wha... But me being on homecoming court

123
00:04:49.915 --> 00:04:51.375
was supposed to be the amuse-bouche

124
00:04:51.458 --> 00:04:53.669
before my triumphant return
to L.A. next semester.

125
00:04:53.752 --> 00:04:55.754
I have my therapist's number at the ready.

126
00:04:55.838 --> 00:04:57.381
I can't pretend this doesn't sting.

127
00:04:58.382 --> 00:05:00.259
I mean. they don't even
have homecoming here.

128
00:05:02.136 --> 00:05:03.554
Oh. my God.

129
00:05:03.637 --> 00:05:04.930
They don't have homecoming here.

130
00:05:05.014 --> 00:05:06.515
-I heard you.
-No.

131
00:05:06.598 --> 00:05:08.851
but that's what I'll do
for my Cosmo video.

132
00:05:08.934 --> 00:05:10.686
I'll give Seattle
the best homecoming of all time

133
00:05:10.769 --> 00:05:12.021
and I'll document the whole thing.

134
00:05:12.104 --> 00:05:14.940
I just have to teach them
what homecoming is all about.

135
00:05:15.024 --> 00:05:16.900
Can you think of anything
more fun and fearless?

136
00:05:16.984 --> 00:05:18.986
[laughs] I actually cannot.

137
00:05:19.069 --> 00:05:20.988
♪ I'm only happy when it rains ♪

138
00:05:21.071 --> 00:05:22.489
[♪ Garbage sings
"I'm Only Happy When It Rains"]

139
00:05:22.573 --> 00:05:26.702
♪ I'm only happy when it's complicated ♪

140
00:05:26.785 --> 00:05:28.704
♪ And though I know you can't ♪

141
00:05:28.787 --> 00:05:30.706
♪ appreciate it ♪

142
00:05:30.789 --> 00:05:33.709
♪ I'm only happy when it rains ♪

143
00:05:34.793 --> 00:05:36.754
♪ Pour your ♪

144
00:05:36.837 --> 00:05:38.756
-♪ misery down ♪
-♪ Pour your misery ♪

145
00:05:38.839 --> 00:05:42.760
-♪ Pour your misery down on me ♪
-♪ down. pour your misery ♪

146
00:05:42.843 --> 00:05:46.764
-♪ Pour your misery down ♪
-♪ down. pour ♪

147
00:05:46.847 --> 00:05:50.768
♪ You can keep me company as long as ♪

148
00:05:50.851 --> 00:05:52.811
♪ you don't care ♪

149
00:05:54.855 --> 00:05:57.733
♪ I'm only happy when it rains ♪

150
00:05:58.859 --> 00:06:02.112
♪ You wanna hear about my new obsession? ♪

151
00:06:02.196 --> 00:06:04.114
♪ I'm riding high upon ♪

152
00:06:04.198 --> 00:06:06.575
♪ a deep depression ♪

153
00:06:06.658 --> 00:06:09.036
♪ I'm only happy when it rains ♪

154
00:06:09.119 --> 00:06:12.623
♪ Pour some misery down on me ♪

155
00:06:12.706 --> 00:06:15.542
♪ I'm only happy when it rains ♪♪

156
00:06:15.626 --> 00:06:17.628
[hip-hop music playing on TV]

157
00:06:25.344 --> 00:06:26.553
Wow.

158
00:06:26.637 --> 00:06:28.514
Did that flautist just do a flip?

159
00:06:28.597 --> 00:06:29.973
Incredible.

160
00:06:34.186 --> 00:06:36.355
[music ends]

161
00:06:39.024 --> 00:06:40.150
As you can see.

162
00:06:40.234 --> 00:06:41.443
homecoming is

163
00:06:41.527 --> 00:06:43.445
a celebration of school spirit.

164
00:06:43.529 --> 00:06:45.280
But. more importantly.

165
00:06:45.364 --> 00:06:47.908
it's a gathering of community.

166
00:06:47.991 --> 00:06:50.994
And. they're really. really fun. you guys.

167
00:06:51.078 --> 00:06:52.454
You've never done one here.

168
00:06:52.538 --> 00:06:54.039
Until now.

169
00:06:54.123 --> 00:06:57.376
I've prepared a 12-point plan
to bring homecoming

170
00:06:57.459 --> 00:06:58.836
to Rainier West High.

171
00:06:58.919 --> 00:07:00.879
There'll be a big game
on the home basketball court.

172
00:07:01.755 --> 00:07:03.340
Obviously.

173
00:07:03.423 --> 00:07:06.510
Cheerleaders. a bonfire.
a king and a queen.

174
00:07:06.593 --> 00:07:08.929
Usually a parade
featuring a minor local celebrity.

175
00:07:09.012 --> 00:07:11.431
Last year. my school had Tom Cruise.

176
00:07:11.515 --> 00:07:13.725
Yes. Kimberly?

177
00:07:13.809 --> 00:07:15.519
We don't have a basketball team here.

178
00:07:15.602 --> 00:07:17.479
And our cheerleaders are neither cheerful

179
00:07:17.563 --> 00:07:18.856
nor leaders.

180
00:07:18.939 --> 00:07:20.816
Okay. uh. what sports

181
00:07:20.899 --> 00:07:22.609
are happening at the school currently?

182
00:07:23.610 --> 00:07:26.029
Well. cross country
has their district championships

183
00:07:26.113 --> 00:07:27.573
this weekend. but--

184
00:07:27.656 --> 00:07:29.741
Great. That'll be the big game then.

185
00:07:29.825 --> 00:07:31.869
With Ms. Burke's

186
00:07:31.952 --> 00:07:32.870
permission.

187
00:07:33.704 --> 00:07:35.789
I'll just infuse some cheer
into the cheerleaders.

188
00:07:35.873 --> 00:07:38.292
and handle all the logistics myself.

189
00:07:38.375 --> 00:07:39.710
Are there any other questions?

190
00:07:39.793 --> 00:07:40.878
This is so dumb.

191
00:07:40.961 --> 00:07:42.921
-That's not a question.
-[Kimberly] Sorry.

192
00:07:43.005 --> 00:07:44.715
Why is this so dumb?

193
00:07:44.798 --> 00:07:46.592
We don't do that kind of thing here.

194
00:07:47.885 --> 00:07:51.722
Well. I counter your question
with another question.

195
00:07:52.848 --> 00:07:53.974
Why not?

196
00:07:54.057 --> 00:07:56.727
We don't like wearing the same color.

197
00:07:56.810 --> 00:07:58.061
We don't like clapping.

198
00:07:58.145 --> 00:08:00.022
We don't chant. That's brainwashing.

199
00:08:00.105 --> 00:08:02.191
by the way. We don't believe in popularity

200
00:08:02.274 --> 00:08:03.317
contests.

201
00:08:04.610 --> 00:08:06.361
We're not conformist.

202
00:08:08.822 --> 00:08:09.907
[whispers] Keep going.

203
00:08:10.866 --> 00:08:12.367
All excellent points. Kimberly.

204
00:08:13.911 --> 00:08:15.537
M-Maybe no to the homecoming court.

205
00:08:15.621 --> 00:08:17.789
but I truly believe

206
00:08:17.873 --> 00:08:21.543
if you actually tried it.
you'd find conformity invigorating.

207
00:08:26.423 --> 00:08:29.760
Okay. I'll do the pep rally.

208
00:08:29.843 --> 00:08:30.719
[Elle] Oh.

209
00:08:31.929 --> 00:08:34.473
You're volunteering
to tackle the pep rally?

210
00:08:34.556 --> 00:08:35.891
Yeah. I know how to do school stuff. too.

211
00:08:35.974 --> 00:08:37.851
so sign me up.

212
00:08:37.935 --> 00:08:40.562
And you're comfortable
with our budgetary constraints?

213
00:08:40.646 --> 00:08:41.939
I mean.

214
00:08:42.022 --> 00:08:45.943
all crafting will have to be 100% DIY.
"Do it yourself."

215
00:08:46.026 --> 00:08:47.569
DIY is not a novel concept here.

216
00:08:47.653 --> 00:08:49.321
But Y will D-I it. right?

217
00:08:49.404 --> 00:08:50.447
Huh?

218
00:08:50.530 --> 00:08:53.492
This isn't some antiestablishment ruse

219
00:08:53.575 --> 00:08:56.161
to humiliate me in front of
the entire school again?

220
00:08:56.245 --> 00:08:58.205
The pep rally will have pep. Elle.

221
00:08:59.957 --> 00:09:01.166
Okay. great.

222
00:09:01.959 --> 00:09:03.293
-Thank you. Kimberly.
-[school bell rings]

223
00:09:05.504 --> 00:09:06.922
Don't forget to read it.

224
00:09:07.005 --> 00:09:08.423
It's really good.

225
00:09:08.507 --> 00:09:11.093
I'm really excited about this DIY thing.

226
00:09:11.176 --> 00:09:14.429
You know. necessity
is the mother of invention.

227
00:09:14.513 --> 00:09:17.099
One time. Sadie Myers' dad lost

228
00:09:17.182 --> 00:09:19.726
all his money producing
a Kevin Costner movie in space.

229
00:09:19.810 --> 00:09:23.855
so she had to have
her tenth birthday party at their house.

230
00:09:23.939 --> 00:09:26.149
And it was actually sort of fun.

231
00:09:26.233 --> 00:09:27.776
In a Little House on the Prairie way.

232
00:09:28.777 --> 00:09:30.696
So. what's going on with you and Dustin?

233
00:09:32.447 --> 00:09:33.573
Oh.

234
00:09:33.657 --> 00:09:35.659
That. Right.

235
00:09:35.742 --> 00:09:36.868
That's over.

236
00:09:36.952 --> 00:09:38.328
In every way.

237
00:09:38.412 --> 00:09:40.122
I'm as single as...

238
00:09:41.748 --> 00:09:43.250
...a girl without a boyfriend.

239
00:09:43.333 --> 00:09:44.668
Samesies.

240
00:09:44.751 --> 00:09:46.253
Wait. what?

241
00:09:46.336 --> 00:09:48.380
Miles and I broke up last night.

242
00:09:49.923 --> 00:09:51.800
It's fine. I'm fine.

243
00:09:51.883 --> 00:09:54.469
Ever since I got back from my New York
trip this summer. it's been strained.

244
00:09:55.178 --> 00:09:56.763
I feel like he was almost...

245
00:09:56.847 --> 00:09:58.390
relieved when I dumped him.

246
00:09:59.558 --> 00:10:01.101
I'm so sorry. Shannon.

247
00:10:01.184 --> 00:10:03.312
It sucks. but you get it.

248
00:10:04.771 --> 00:10:06.273
Because of Dustin.

249
00:10:07.441 --> 00:10:09.693
Of course. I'm devastated.

250
00:10:09.776 --> 00:10:13.238
but we were barely together 48 hours.

251
00:10:13.322 --> 00:10:14.990
If we were sushi.
you could still safely eat us.

252
00:10:15.073 --> 00:10:16.074
You guys were

253
00:10:16.158 --> 00:10:18.035
together. what?

254
00:10:18.118 --> 00:10:19.619
Two years.

255
00:10:20.495 --> 00:10:22.039
I really am okay. though.

256
00:10:22.122 --> 00:10:23.332
It was my choice.

257
00:10:25.083 --> 00:10:27.544
[percussive music playing]

258
00:10:28.795 --> 00:10:29.796
Hey. Dustin.

259
00:10:29.880 --> 00:10:31.006
Hey.

260
00:10:31.089 --> 00:10:32.424
I catch you with that inside again.

261
00:10:32.507 --> 00:10:33.925
it is Saturday detention.

262
00:10:36.219 --> 00:10:37.429
Whatever.

263
00:10:38.764 --> 00:10:40.057
[lunch lady] Next.

264
00:10:40.140 --> 00:10:41.224
Here you go.

265
00:10:42.142 --> 00:10:43.477
Hey. Lizbian.

266
00:10:44.478 --> 00:10:46.146
-Huh?
-Hey. Lizbian.

267
00:10:46.229 --> 00:10:47.564
-Um...
-What's up?

268
00:10:51.568 --> 00:10:55.072
Thank you for teaching me
more about matriarchal societies.

269
00:10:57.366 --> 00:10:59.618
You read my zine.

270
00:10:59.701 --> 00:11:00.869
I always read your zine.

271
00:11:06.708 --> 00:11:07.793
What is this?

272
00:11:07.876 --> 00:11:09.753
I'm making conversation.

273
00:11:09.836 --> 00:11:10.879
With a friend.

274
00:11:11.880 --> 00:11:14.299
Or Principal Anderson is a crook

275
00:11:14.383 --> 00:11:16.218
and you want my permission

276
00:11:16.301 --> 00:11:17.803
to turn the school against him.

277
00:11:17.886 --> 00:11:19.679
I actually wanted to apologize.

278
00:11:21.681 --> 00:11:24.518
I let my disdain for the guy
get the best of me

279
00:11:24.601 --> 00:11:26.895
and I... I screwed up.

280
00:11:26.978 --> 00:11:28.855
Royally.

281
00:11:30.649 --> 00:11:31.858
You should keep digging.

282
00:11:33.985 --> 00:11:37.697
I don't want to go to a school
run by a corrupt thief anyway.

283
00:11:39.616 --> 00:11:40.450
So. are you apologizing

284
00:11:40.534 --> 00:11:41.785
because you actually mean it

285
00:11:41.868 --> 00:11:43.620
or because Elle forced you to?

286
00:11:43.703 --> 00:11:45.288
Nah. I'm serious.

287
00:11:45.372 --> 00:11:47.541
If I'd known I was putting you
at risk of getting kicked out.

288
00:11:47.624 --> 00:11:49.334
I never would've been so public.

289
00:11:49.418 --> 00:11:51.586
Plus Elle was. like. really mad at you.

290
00:11:51.670 --> 00:11:53.255
Yeah. I didn't know anger

291
00:11:53.338 --> 00:11:55.298
was an emotion she could feel.

292
00:11:55.382 --> 00:11:57.300
It's… really quite upsetting.

293
00:11:57.384 --> 00:11:58.969
Terrifying.

294
00:12:00.554 --> 00:12:01.930
[sighs]

295
00:12:04.683 --> 00:12:07.018
It's just not quite right.

296
00:12:07.102 --> 00:12:10.981
[sighs]
Woods women do not look good in green.

297
00:12:11.064 --> 00:12:13.024
But it's your school color.

298
00:12:13.108 --> 00:12:14.734
and you're gonna be on camera tomorrow.

299
00:12:14.818 --> 00:12:18.196
so persist we must. Here.

300
00:12:19.364 --> 00:12:20.574
Let's see you in a forest.

301
00:12:20.657 --> 00:12:22.200
You're a lifesaver. Mom.

302
00:12:22.284 --> 00:12:24.286
Oh. I mean. this is important.

303
00:12:24.369 --> 00:12:27.998
I mean. they say fun. fearless female. but

304
00:12:28.081 --> 00:12:31.751
fashion is implied in all of those words.

305
00:12:31.835 --> 00:12:33.545
I really need this to go well.

306
00:12:33.628 --> 00:12:35.005
I need the video to be so good

307
00:12:35.088 --> 00:12:37.674
that I'm a no-brainer for the internship.

308
00:12:38.884 --> 00:12:40.093
[gasps softly]

309
00:12:40.177 --> 00:12:41.344
Oh...

310
00:12:43.138 --> 00:12:44.431
[whines]

311
00:12:44.514 --> 00:12:46.892
Bruiser. I never should've doubted you.

312
00:12:46.975 --> 00:12:49.811
I mean. not only
are you gonna win this thing.

313
00:12:49.895 --> 00:12:52.189
but you might've just convinced me
to start wearing green.

314
00:12:54.441 --> 00:12:55.525
You okay?

315
00:12:59.779 --> 00:13:01.031
Um...

316
00:13:02.824 --> 00:13:05.118
I kind of like someone here

317
00:13:05.202 --> 00:13:07.537
who I really. really can't like.

318
00:13:07.621 --> 00:13:09.789
Is it unrequited? [scoffs]

319
00:13:09.873 --> 00:13:11.833
How could it be unrequited?
You're Elle Woods.

320
00:13:11.917 --> 00:13:13.502
I'm sorry I said that.

321
00:13:13.585 --> 00:13:15.545
No. it's...

322
00:13:15.629 --> 00:13:17.339
complicated.

323
00:13:18.340 --> 00:13:20.509
But how do you un-like someone?

324
00:13:21.593 --> 00:13:22.594
Hmm.

325
00:13:23.929 --> 00:13:27.265
Well. it helps if they do
something really bad to you.

326
00:13:27.349 --> 00:13:30.018
Like when Marlena
was possessed by the devil.

327
00:13:30.101 --> 00:13:32.896
it was really hard
for John to stay attracted to her.

328
00:13:32.979 --> 00:13:34.481
But that's not a perfect example.

329
00:13:34.564 --> 00:13:36.149
He still loved her.

330
00:13:36.233 --> 00:13:37.359
He exorcised her.

331
00:13:37.442 --> 00:13:38.944
You're right.

332
00:13:40.654 --> 00:13:42.531
Honestly. in my experience.

333
00:13:42.614 --> 00:13:45.492
if you really like someone.

334
00:13:45.575 --> 00:13:46.910
it's kind of undeniable.

335
00:13:48.245 --> 00:13:50.080
It's like a fast-moving train.

336
00:13:51.581 --> 00:13:54.292
Well. I definitely need
to get off this train.

337
00:13:54.376 --> 00:13:56.545
That's why you need to win this contest.

338
00:13:56.628 --> 00:13:58.547
so you can go back to L.A.

339
00:13:59.714 --> 00:14:03.385
Now. we need a fun. fearless attitude.

340
00:14:03.468 --> 00:14:05.387
Let's go brew a pot of oolong

341
00:14:05.470 --> 00:14:07.138
and put on our Tony Robbins mix.

342
00:14:08.765 --> 00:14:10.141
I'm gonna try this one on.

343
00:14:10.225 --> 00:14:11.351
It'll probably fit.

344
00:14:11.434 --> 00:14:13.436
[upbeat music playing]

345
00:14:15.814 --> 00:14:17.148
Hey. Elle-A.

346
00:14:19.526 --> 00:14:20.860
I have to show you something.

347
00:14:22.070 --> 00:14:23.488
[Elle scoffs] What are we doing?

348
00:14:24.489 --> 00:14:25.448
[Dustin] What do you see?

349
00:14:25.532 --> 00:14:28.243
[Elle] A haven for people
who don't like human interaction.

350
00:14:29.369 --> 00:14:30.745
Computers. Mouses.

351
00:14:31.413 --> 00:14:32.247
No mousepads.

352
00:14:34.457 --> 00:14:35.709
Mouses or mice?

353
00:14:35.792 --> 00:14:36.918
Missing.

354
00:14:37.002 --> 00:14:39.629
The school budget.
which Anderson single-handedly oversees.

355
00:14:39.713 --> 00:14:42.841
said we spent $129
on mousepads last month.

356
00:14:43.633 --> 00:14:45.760
-But no mousepads.
-Just like we're supposed to have

357
00:14:45.844 --> 00:14:47.637
a nurse three days a week.
but she's only in on Thursdays.

358
00:14:47.721 --> 00:14:49.848
Okay. what about earthquake insurance?

359
00:14:49.931 --> 00:14:51.433
-That seems legitimate.
-Great.

360
00:14:51.516 --> 00:14:54.185
In the unlikely event the school
collapses in an earthquake. we're saved.

361
00:14:54.269 --> 00:14:55.979
Otherwise. we're screwed.

362
00:14:56.062 --> 00:14:57.939
Wait. even if I agree
that this all appears shady...

363
00:14:58.023 --> 00:14:59.190
Which you do.

364
00:14:59.274 --> 00:15:00.442
...we can't pursue it.

365
00:15:01.234 --> 00:15:03.028
You know how I feel about protecting Liz.

366
00:15:03.111 --> 00:15:04.362
I apologized.

367
00:15:04.446 --> 00:15:05.989
She told me to go for it.

368
00:15:06.072 --> 00:15:07.782
Wait. you apologized?

369
00:15:08.700 --> 00:15:09.701
For yourself?

370
00:15:10.869 --> 00:15:12.454
I got carried away.

371
00:15:12.537 --> 00:15:14.289
I...

372
00:15:14.372 --> 00:15:16.541
owned it and we're good.

373
00:15:17.417 --> 00:15:19.085
That shows integrity.

374
00:15:20.378 --> 00:15:21.921
So why do you look confused?

375
00:15:22.672 --> 00:15:23.548
I don't.

376
00:15:25.634 --> 00:15:27.302
Anyway. I should go.

377
00:15:27.385 --> 00:15:28.887
Got to get to class.

378
00:15:28.970 --> 00:15:31.264
Big rally this afternoon.

379
00:15:31.348 --> 00:15:33.266
There might be swooping hawks.

380
00:15:33.350 --> 00:15:34.476
Okay. bye.

381
00:15:40.273 --> 00:15:43.109
Okay. runners. attention please.

382
00:15:43.193 --> 00:15:45.028
Everyone's piling into the gym now.

383
00:15:45.111 --> 00:15:47.405
Once the clock hits 3:15 on the dot.

384
00:15:47.489 --> 00:15:49.699
we'll run in. I'll hit play
on "Cotton Eye Joe."

385
00:15:49.783 --> 00:15:51.618
and everyone will be
cheering their faces off.

386
00:15:51.701 --> 00:15:52.619
Then we'll announce your names--

387
00:15:52.702 --> 00:15:54.496
-[Eva] Boom!
-Hi. Oh. Hi.

388
00:15:54.579 --> 00:15:56.623
Sorry. sorry. I think that's...

389
00:15:57.957 --> 00:16:00.502
Back to the top.
Or wherever you're comfortable.

390
00:16:00.585 --> 00:16:01.670
Okay.

391
00:16:01.753 --> 00:16:03.421
Anyway. we'll all go in

392
00:16:03.505 --> 00:16:05.048
and we'll announce your names one by one.

393
00:16:05.131 --> 00:16:06.383
starting with Miles.

394
00:16:07.342 --> 00:16:09.260
Who's late. by the way. Where is he?

395
00:16:09.344 --> 00:16:10.470
He might not come.

396
00:16:11.429 --> 00:16:12.430
Why would he do that?

397
00:16:12.514 --> 00:16:14.307
He volunteers
at an animal shelter on Thursdays.

398
00:16:15.350 --> 00:16:16.601
He's usually late to practice.

399
00:16:16.685 --> 00:16:17.977
[Elle] Okay.

400
00:16:18.061 --> 00:16:21.398
That's a very neutral.
not at all appealing thing for him to do.

401
00:16:21.481 --> 00:16:23.900
I have no response to that whatsoever.

402
00:16:23.983 --> 00:16:26.277
Great. We'll all run in.

403
00:16:26.361 --> 00:16:28.405
there'll be instantly iconic speeches.

404
00:16:28.488 --> 00:16:30.281
banners. streamers. vendors.

405
00:16:30.365 --> 00:16:32.325
fingers crossed on some swooping hawks.

406
00:16:32.409 --> 00:16:34.828
[gasps] Maybe a balloon arch.

407
00:16:34.911 --> 00:16:36.996
Oh. it's time. Okay.

408
00:16:37.080 --> 00:16:38.748
Rainier West High Runners.

409
00:16:38.832 --> 00:16:41.501
-are you ready to get your pep on?
-[mouthing]

410
00:16:41.584 --> 00:16:42.669
Come on!

411
00:16:42.752 --> 00:16:45.255
[energetic music playing]

412
00:16:46.339 --> 00:16:47.549
Woo-hoo!

413
00:16:49.217 --> 00:16:50.677
Make some noise!

414
00:16:50.760 --> 00:16:52.178
Whoo!

415
00:16:56.057 --> 00:16:57.058
[music turns off]

416
00:16:58.184 --> 00:16:59.769
Where is everybody?

417
00:16:59.853 --> 00:17:01.521
-[scoffs]
-Um...

418
00:17:01.604 --> 00:17:02.689
Oh. my God.

419
00:17:04.441 --> 00:17:05.817
I'm sorry. Elle.

420
00:17:05.900 --> 00:17:07.444
Kimberly said she had this.

421
00:17:14.409 --> 00:17:15.702
Kimberly?

422
00:17:15.785 --> 00:17:16.953
This is a disaster.

423
00:17:17.746 --> 00:17:18.997
What's with the camera crew?

424
00:17:19.080 --> 00:17:20.373
Stay in focus. Stop.

425
00:17:20.457 --> 00:17:23.626
Uh. they're recording this
for posterity. Never mind.

426
00:17:23.710 --> 00:17:25.044
What happened?

427
00:17:25.128 --> 00:17:27.046
Where are the decorations?
Where are the posters?

428
00:17:27.130 --> 00:17:28.047
Where is everyone?

429
00:17:28.131 --> 00:17:29.299
You said you'd spread the word.

430
00:17:29.382 --> 00:17:30.300
I did.

431
00:17:30.383 --> 00:17:31.885
I used that computer thing.

432
00:17:31.968 --> 00:17:32.927
Email.

433
00:17:33.011 --> 00:17:34.637
Nobody uses email.

434
00:17:34.721 --> 00:17:36.681
You might as well
have sent a carrier pigeon.

435
00:17:36.765 --> 00:17:38.391
Email. seriously?

436
00:17:38.475 --> 00:17:40.477
-That's really messed up.
-Okay. how was I supposed to know

437
00:17:40.560 --> 00:17:42.812
that no one would check
their. like. computers?

438
00:17:42.896 --> 00:17:44.773
You did this on purpose.

439
00:17:44.856 --> 00:17:46.274
Why?

440
00:17:46.357 --> 00:17:47.817
Because she doesn't like me.

441
00:17:52.155 --> 00:17:55.408
Never mind. I will figure out
the rest of homecoming

442
00:17:55.492 --> 00:17:57.202
by myself.

443
00:17:57.285 --> 00:17:58.578
[Eva] Boom.

444
00:18:01.831 --> 00:18:03.291
Mom. can you not. please?

445
00:18:03.374 --> 00:18:04.375
Honey. but this is

446
00:18:04.459 --> 00:18:07.337
your "all is lost" moment.

447
00:18:07.420 --> 00:18:10.423
It's when our heroine
rises from the ashes.

448
00:18:10.507 --> 00:18:13.009
like a fun. fearless female would.

449
00:18:16.304 --> 00:18:17.847
Right.

450
00:18:19.265 --> 00:18:20.391
Thank you. Oysters.

451
00:18:20.475 --> 00:18:22.936
for your vulnerability.

452
00:18:23.019 --> 00:18:24.354
We're done here.

453
00:18:24.437 --> 00:18:26.439
[indistinct chatter]

454
00:18:28.650 --> 00:18:29.776
[Shannon sighs]

455
00:18:32.320 --> 00:18:34.113
That was very uncool.

456
00:18:34.197 --> 00:18:35.198
Can I help?

457
00:18:36.449 --> 00:18:38.201
I don't even know where to start.

458
00:18:39.869 --> 00:18:41.037
I want to show you something.

459
00:18:42.539 --> 00:18:44.040
I'm intrigued.

460
00:18:47.669 --> 00:18:48.837
You were so right.

461
00:18:48.920 --> 00:18:51.005
The whipped cream
takes this Frappuccino to the next level.

462
00:18:51.089 --> 00:18:52.924
I know. they should make them this way.

463
00:18:53.007 --> 00:18:54.676
Mm-hmm. Mm.

464
00:18:55.718 --> 00:18:57.887
So. my mom likes to bring me

465
00:18:57.971 --> 00:19:01.558
to this place because
sometimes you can see Mt. Rainier.

466
00:19:01.641 --> 00:19:02.976
and sometimes you can't.

467
00:19:03.726 --> 00:19:06.020
And when we're here on the cloudy days.

468
00:19:06.104 --> 00:19:07.689
my mom always says.

469
00:19:07.772 --> 00:19:09.732
"I bet we'll see it tomorrow."

470
00:19:12.068 --> 00:19:15.113
As a naturally glass half-full person.
I deeply relate.

471
00:19:18.491 --> 00:19:21.077
Though my glass is feeling
a little emptier today.

472
00:19:23.288 --> 00:19:24.289
[sighs]

473
00:19:24.372 --> 00:19:26.457
I really need
this homecoming to be perfect.

474
00:19:26.541 --> 00:19:29.127
but I'm starting to feel like
it was a terrible idea.

475
00:19:31.796 --> 00:19:33.882
Kimberly can actually
be a really good friend.

476
00:19:33.965 --> 00:19:36.426
Her homelife isn't great. so

477
00:19:36.509 --> 00:19:39.554
she's got some insecurities
that can make her kind of...

478
00:19:39.637 --> 00:19:40.889
Monstrous?

479
00:19:44.601 --> 00:19:45.602
[laughs]

480
00:19:48.104 --> 00:19:50.398
Homecoming wasn't a terrible idea.

481
00:19:50.481 --> 00:19:52.984
But Seattle's a little more

482
00:19:53.067 --> 00:19:54.193
grassroots.

483
00:19:54.986 --> 00:19:56.613
People are quirky.

484
00:19:56.696 --> 00:19:58.990
They're really afraid
of being like everyone else.

485
00:19:59.824 --> 00:20:01.618
Except when it comes to plaid.

486
00:20:02.994 --> 00:20:04.537
I've known you for. like. five minutes.

487
00:20:04.621 --> 00:20:07.373
but you're a force.

488
00:20:07.457 --> 00:20:08.625
I feel like you can do this.

489
00:20:09.751 --> 00:20:11.836
But we have no budget. no concessions.

490
00:20:11.920 --> 00:20:13.713
Cirque du Soleil isn't returning my calls.

491
00:20:13.796 --> 00:20:16.507
I know in L.A. you're used to...

492
00:20:16.591 --> 00:20:18.468
Harrison Ford
coming to your birthday party

493
00:20:18.551 --> 00:20:20.219
-or whatever--
-It was a Halloween party

494
00:20:20.303 --> 00:20:24.140
and he came dressed as Indiana Jones.
which felt a little first thought.

495
00:20:25.224 --> 00:20:27.185
We can do homecoming.

496
00:20:27.268 --> 00:20:31.272
It might just not be like
an L.A. homecoming.

497
00:20:31.356 --> 00:20:33.399
People are creative here.

498
00:20:33.483 --> 00:20:36.277
Maybe let them do it
their way instead of your way.

499
00:20:37.612 --> 00:20:39.238
That might be really amazing. too.

500
00:20:41.783 --> 00:20:43.159
To homecoming.

501
00:20:43.242 --> 00:20:44.494
[Elle] To homecoming.

502
00:20:44.577 --> 00:20:46.329
[♪ The Dylans play "Planet Love"]

503
00:20:54.796 --> 00:20:58.257
So. homecoming still needs a DJ/announcer.

504
00:20:58.341 --> 00:21:00.927
And I'm thinking.
do I have any wonderful friends

505
00:21:01.010 --> 00:21:03.972
with commanding voices
and great taste in music?

506
00:21:05.348 --> 00:21:07.225
Are you gonna micromanage my playlist

507
00:21:07.308 --> 00:21:09.102
and eventually DJ the homecoming yourself?

508
00:21:09.185 --> 00:21:11.187
No. you can play whatever you want.

509
00:21:11.270 --> 00:21:13.189
Completely up to you.

510
00:21:13.272 --> 00:21:14.649
Did you hit your head again?

511
00:21:14.732 --> 00:21:17.777
♪ I hang my star on you...

512
00:21:17.860 --> 00:21:19.862
[Donna] Okay. 12 dozen brownies

513
00:21:19.946 --> 00:21:22.240
and the place smells like
the Keebler factory.

514
00:21:22.323 --> 00:21:23.992
Do you think this'll be enough?

515
00:21:24.075 --> 00:21:25.410
You're a saint. Donna.

516
00:21:26.119 --> 00:21:28.746
I should put pot in one of 'em.

517
00:21:28.830 --> 00:21:30.164
Just for fun.

518
00:21:30.248 --> 00:21:31.624
You know.
like Willy Wonka's chocolate bars.

519
00:21:31.708 --> 00:21:33.501
Mom. this is a school function.

520
00:21:33.584 --> 00:21:34.752
No. that's good. actually.

521
00:21:36.629 --> 00:21:38.756
Not your mom drugging children.

522
00:21:38.840 --> 00:21:41.092
Just. you know. the suggestion of it.

523
00:21:42.468 --> 00:21:44.846
Friends. stoners.
come to the homecoming race

524
00:21:44.929 --> 00:21:46.180
this weekend.

525
00:21:46.264 --> 00:21:48.307
My mom's famous brownies.

526
00:21:48.391 --> 00:21:50.643
One of them has something
that you. specifically.

527
00:21:50.727 --> 00:21:52.812
might like.

