00:33:41.270 --> 00:33:43.522
♪ Never was a cornflake girl...

791
00:33:43.605 --> 00:33:46.483
Go. Miles! Go! Run!

792
00:33:46.567 --> 00:33:48.318
♪ Thought that was a good solution...

793
00:33:48.402 --> 00:33:50.529
Go! You got this. kid! Go. go!

794
00:33:50.612 --> 00:33:52.239
Go. Miles. go. run!

795
00:33:52.322 --> 00:33:54.450
Run faster! Beat 'em!

796
00:33:54.533 --> 00:33:58.120
♪ This is not really happening ♪

797
00:33:59.496 --> 00:34:02.916
♪ You bet your life it is ♪

798
00:34:03.751 --> 00:34:06.879
♪ Oh. honey. you bet your life ♪

799
00:34:06.962 --> 00:34:12.134
♪ It's a peel out the watchword ♪

800
00:34:12.217 --> 00:34:14.511
♪ Rabbit ♪

801
00:34:15.512 --> 00:34:18.265
♪ where'd you put the keys. girl? ♪

802
00:34:19.433 --> 00:34:21.477
♪ Rabbit ♪

803
00:34:22.686 --> 00:34:24.646
♪ where'd you put the keys? ♪♪

804
00:34:25.939 --> 00:34:27.524
Way to go. buddy.

805
00:34:28.817 --> 00:34:30.319
Amazing!

806
00:34:30.402 --> 00:34:32.404
I love sports!

807
00:34:32.488 --> 00:34:33.864
Who knew?

808
00:34:36.116 --> 00:34:38.202
Hey.

809
00:34:38.285 --> 00:34:39.745
That was incredible.

810
00:34:39.828 --> 00:34:40.829
Thanks. [laughs]

811
00:34:40.913 --> 00:34:42.664
I didn't know trying
could be so rewarding.

812
00:34:42.748 --> 00:34:44.583
Yeah. trying rocks.

813
00:34:44.666 --> 00:34:46.251
Uh. I'll see you guys. okay?

814
00:34:46.335 --> 00:34:47.586
Bye.

815
00:34:47.669 --> 00:34:50.506
Elle. we made $300 on concessions

816
00:34:50.589 --> 00:34:53.383
and Anderson said
the student activities board can have it.

817
00:34:53.467 --> 00:34:54.927
I have an idea.

818
00:34:55.010 --> 00:34:56.804
We buy one and a half pairs of jeans?

819
00:34:56.887 --> 00:34:58.931
A winter formal.

820
00:34:59.014 --> 00:35:00.432
A winter formal?

821
00:35:00.516 --> 00:35:01.850
Like.

822
00:35:01.934 --> 00:35:03.101
where people do their hair

823
00:35:03.185 --> 00:35:05.938
and wear fancy dresses and... not plaid?

824
00:35:06.730 --> 00:35:07.981
Maybe less plaid.

825
00:35:08.065 --> 00:35:10.067
We've never had one before.
but we've never

826
00:35:10.150 --> 00:35:12.903
had one of these either.
and this was so fun.

827
00:35:14.112 --> 00:35:15.405
I was thinking you and I
could plan it together.

828
00:35:15.489 --> 00:35:16.990
Yes. Okay.

829
00:35:17.074 --> 00:35:18.784
I'm thinking ice sculptures.

830
00:35:18.867 --> 00:35:19.952
I'm thinking fake snow machines.

831
00:35:20.035 --> 00:35:21.411
-I'm thinking--
-[Kimberly] Shannon.

832
00:35:21.495 --> 00:35:22.746
Let's go.

833
00:35:22.830 --> 00:35:24.289
I'm gonna drop off the petty cash

834
00:35:24.373 --> 00:35:25.666
-at the school.
-Okay.

835
00:35:26.750 --> 00:35:28.210
Hey. Shannon.

836
00:35:29.586 --> 00:35:31.630
The mountain came out today.

837
00:35:31.713 --> 00:35:33.090
Byes!

838
00:35:50.607 --> 00:35:52.192
[Miles] Can I help?

839
00:35:52.276 --> 00:35:54.236
[Elle] O-Oh.

840
00:35:54.319 --> 00:35:56.154
Sure. Yeah.

841
00:35:56.238 --> 00:35:59.366
There's some signage
by the entrance at the woods.

842
00:35:59.449 --> 00:36:01.368
My... my dad helped me put it up.

843
00:36:02.244 --> 00:36:03.412
Okay. yeah.

844
00:36:05.330 --> 00:36:06.748
Yeah.

845
00:36:06.832 --> 00:36:08.834
[wistful music playing]

846
00:36:10.544 --> 00:36:12.254
-[Miles] That's tough. yeah.
-[Elle laughs]

847
00:36:12.337 --> 00:36:14.298
-Great race. by the way.
-Thank you.

848
00:36:14.381 --> 00:36:17.676
What you did at the end there--
that was pretty epic.

849
00:36:17.759 --> 00:36:19.595
Well... to be honest.

850
00:36:19.678 --> 00:36:22.556
it's the first time I've run
in front of that many people. so...

851
00:36:31.148 --> 00:36:32.274
♪ Ta-da ♪♪

852
00:36:32.357 --> 00:36:33.483
Very impressive.

853
00:36:34.276 --> 00:36:35.736
I'm a pro.

854
00:36:37.487 --> 00:36:38.614
You're very sparkly.

855
00:36:38.697 --> 00:36:40.240
It's an oil-free shimmer.

856
00:36:40.324 --> 00:36:43.327
and it is unisex. if you're interested.
[chuckles]

857
00:36:44.870 --> 00:36:46.496
You know. I think it's gonna rain.

858
00:36:46.580 --> 00:36:47.748
Here.

859
00:36:47.831 --> 00:36:48.999
Stand under the tree.

860
00:36:49.917 --> 00:36:51.043
Take this.

861
00:36:51.126 --> 00:36:52.586
-[mutters]
-[giggles]

862
00:36:52.669 --> 00:36:54.087
There you go.

863
00:37:00.344 --> 00:37:01.929
[rain falling]

864
00:37:03.430 --> 00:37:05.599
Okay. how did you know that?

865
00:37:06.600 --> 00:37:08.226
Live here long enough.
you can just kind of feel it.

866
00:37:09.811 --> 00:37:11.271
Don't you get tired of all the rain?

867
00:37:12.314 --> 00:37:13.565
No.

868
00:37:14.524 --> 00:37:15.984
I mean. people complain about Seattle

869
00:37:16.068 --> 00:37:19.446
being. like. dark and depressing. but

870
00:37:19.529 --> 00:37:21.239
the rain is actually
what makes it beautiful.

871
00:37:22.366 --> 00:37:23.575
It's what makes it green.

872
00:37:29.081 --> 00:37:30.415
Sorry.

873
00:37:31.959 --> 00:37:33.126
-Here.
-Oh.

874
00:37:33.210 --> 00:37:34.252
I got it.

875
00:37:42.344 --> 00:37:44.221
So. you and Dustin...

876
00:37:45.555 --> 00:37:47.307
If I'm being perfectly honest...

877
00:37:49.267 --> 00:37:51.269
[whispers] ...we were never
actually dating.

878
00:37:53.689 --> 00:37:56.358
[regular volume] Kimberly thought
I had a crush on somebody else.

879
00:37:58.110 --> 00:37:59.403
Crush on who?

880
00:38:02.489 --> 00:38:03.824
Um...

881
00:38:05.283 --> 00:38:06.785
[laughs]

882
00:38:06.868 --> 00:38:09.413
I'm unable to disclose that information

883
00:38:09.496 --> 00:38:10.956
at this moment.

884
00:38:11.039 --> 00:38:13.041
[tender music playing]

885
00:38:14.751 --> 00:38:16.044
[Eva] And even though

886
00:38:16.128 --> 00:38:17.838
the big game is over.

887
00:38:17.921 --> 00:38:20.841
our fun. fearless female

888
00:38:20.924 --> 00:38:22.259
-never stops.
-Oh. my God. Mom.

889
00:38:22.342 --> 00:38:23.719
Here she is. cleaning up

890
00:38:23.802 --> 00:38:26.263
with our star quarterback.

891
00:38:26.346 --> 00:38:27.973
I'm sorry. it's this

892
00:38:28.056 --> 00:38:30.434
-dumb video project we're doing.
-[Miles] It's-it's okay.

893
00:38:30.517 --> 00:38:32.561
I should probably go.
My-my dads are here. They...

894
00:38:32.644 --> 00:38:33.729
-Yeah.
-They're gonna drive me home.

895
00:38:34.604 --> 00:38:35.439
-Okay.
-Okay.

896
00:38:35.522 --> 00:38:36.440
Bye.

897
00:38:36.523 --> 00:38:38.483
-Bye.
-And... that's a cut.

898
00:38:39.776 --> 00:38:41.069
All right. guys. you can take five.

899
00:38:41.153 --> 00:38:42.696
-Make it a real five.
-Can I have that tape. please?

900
00:38:44.865 --> 00:38:47.159
-And put a tarp over the camera. Joe.
-You got it. Mrs. Woods.

901
00:38:47.242 --> 00:38:48.452
Mom. what was that?

902
00:38:48.535 --> 00:38:50.871
We just got the most amazing footage.

903
00:38:50.954 --> 00:38:53.415
This isn't footage. this is my life.

904
00:38:54.291 --> 00:38:55.792
I... I know.

905
00:38:55.876 --> 00:38:56.710
You know what. forget this.

906
00:38:56.793 --> 00:38:59.254
-Wait. wait. what are you doing?
-I don't want to do the contest anymore.

907
00:38:59.337 --> 00:39:01.673
No. Elle. we can win this thing.

908
00:39:01.757 --> 00:39:04.426
I already renewed
our subscription to the Bowl.

909
00:39:04.509 --> 00:39:06.053
You did this for yourself.

910
00:39:06.887 --> 00:39:07.929
What?

911
00:39:08.013 --> 00:39:10.557
You pretended
to be doing the video for me.

912
00:39:10.640 --> 00:39:13.935
but clearly. you were just
dying to get back to L.A. yourself.

913
00:39:14.019 --> 00:39:17.647
Okay. maybe I'm not loving

914
00:39:17.731 --> 00:39:20.067
Seattle. and I was intrigued

915
00:39:20.150 --> 00:39:22.527
by the idea of having a reason
to go back home.

916
00:39:22.611 --> 00:39:24.362
Yeah. because you're so closed-minded.

917
00:39:24.446 --> 00:39:25.947
you can't look around
and say maybe this place

918
00:39:26.031 --> 00:39:27.532
doesn't suck.

919
00:39:27.616 --> 00:39:30.577
Maybe it's okay people don't do things
here like they do in L.A.

920
00:39:30.660 --> 00:39:33.121
Okay. you're the one that wanted
to go back to L.A. in the first place.

921
00:39:33.205 --> 00:39:34.539
Well. now I don't know!

922
00:39:35.582 --> 00:39:39.336
I'm changing this place.
and maybe it's changing me. too.

923
00:39:39.419 --> 00:39:41.755
And I don't totally hate it.

924
00:39:41.838 --> 00:39:43.173
I don't need to pretend

925
00:39:43.256 --> 00:39:46.051
to be fun and fearless for a stupid video.

926
00:39:47.677 --> 00:39:50.597
I am fun and fearless.

927
00:39:51.598 --> 00:39:53.725
[♪ Mazzy Star play "Bells Ring"]

928
00:39:53.809 --> 00:39:57.437
You can't walk home. Elle.
It's two miles and it's raining.

929
00:39:59.314 --> 00:40:00.816
Fearless!

930
00:40:01.900 --> 00:40:04.111
[thunder rumbling]

931
00:40:10.325 --> 00:40:12.410
Oh. my poor shoes.

932
00:40:22.921 --> 00:40:27.175
♪ Bells ring into the night ♪

933
00:40:28.718 --> 00:40:33.515
♪ Sounds like a mistress
on a rainy night...

934
00:40:34.891 --> 00:40:36.726
[Chad] I am so glad
you didn't have to run in this.

935
00:40:36.810 --> 00:40:39.563
♪ down together...

936
00:40:39.646 --> 00:40:41.356
Uh. I'm just gonna be a second.

937
00:40:41.439 --> 00:40:42.858
-All right.
-I'll be quick.

938
00:40:42.941 --> 00:40:44.651
♪ goes away...

939
00:40:46.778 --> 00:40:48.488
Did you walk home?

940
00:40:48.572 --> 00:40:50.157
My-my dads could've given you a ride.

941
00:40:52.409 --> 00:40:54.411
I still have your jacket.

942
00:40:54.494 --> 00:40:57.289
It's pouring.
Just give it back to me tomorrow.

943
00:41:12.304 --> 00:41:16.766
♪ Don't want to say
that I'm through with it ♪

944
00:41:18.059 --> 00:41:22.564
♪ Just want to be right by your side ♪

945
00:41:24.566 --> 00:41:29.571
♪ Right by your side ♪♪

946
00:41:54.888 --> 00:41:56.264
Mom?

947
00:41:56.348 --> 00:41:58.266
[Wyatt] Hey. there.

948
00:41:58.350 --> 00:42:00.518
Looks like you got trapped in the rain.

949
00:42:00.602 --> 00:42:02.187
-Where's Mom?
-Uh. she. apparently.

950
00:42:02.270 --> 00:42:04.856
is helping out the superintendent
with his mayoral campaign.

951
00:42:04.940 --> 00:42:06.900
She was very riled up
about elastic waistbands.

952
00:42:06.983 --> 00:42:09.903
Okay. Do you know when she'll be back?

953
00:42:09.986 --> 00:42:12.572
I really. really need to talk to her.

954
00:42:13.949 --> 00:42:15.325
You could talk to me.

955
00:42:19.579 --> 00:42:21.039
Like...

956
00:42:22.374 --> 00:42:23.541
Like. about my life?

957
00:42:23.625 --> 00:42:26.419
Then you'll give me your opinion on it?

958
00:42:26.503 --> 00:42:27.963
Sure.

959
00:42:28.046 --> 00:42:29.965
I mean. I was kind of bummed
when I found out

960
00:42:30.048 --> 00:42:31.174
that you were thinking about going back

961
00:42:31.258 --> 00:42:33.468
to Los Angeles without even
talking to me about it first.

962
00:42:33.551 --> 00:42:35.470
-That's not happening anymore.
-Oh.

963
00:42:35.553 --> 00:42:37.681
I just kissed a guy
who got broken up with by a girl

964
00:42:37.764 --> 00:42:39.432
who I'm really trying to become
friends with. and obviously.

965
00:42:39.516 --> 00:42:41.059
I shouldn't have done that.
but it was really. really hard

966
00:42:41.142 --> 00:42:42.686
not to. so what should I do?

967
00:42:50.485 --> 00:42:52.112
Uh...

968
00:42:52.195 --> 00:42:53.280
I'll just go wait for Mom.

969
00:42:53.363 --> 00:42:54.489
Great.

970
00:42:56.700 --> 00:42:58.118
[exhales sharply]

971
00:43:00.870 --> 00:43:02.455
No.

972
00:43:03.999 --> 00:43:06.459
[muttering]

973
00:43:06.543 --> 00:43:10.130
"How long do I have to wait before
I'm allowed to kiss a friend's ex?"

974
00:43:10.213 --> 00:43:12.299
This one says...

975
00:43:12.382 --> 00:43:13.717
two years.

976
00:43:13.800 --> 00:43:17.012
That one says
the length of the relationship

977
00:43:17.095 --> 00:43:18.638
plus two years.

978
00:43:18.722 --> 00:43:20.181
I'm seeing...

979
00:43:21.599 --> 00:43:23.226
"...never. you monster."

980
00:43:23.310 --> 00:43:25.145
Triple-checking for one

981
00:43:25.228 --> 00:43:27.147
that says 48 hours.

982
00:43:27.230 --> 00:43:28.648
What if you're really new friends?

983
00:43:28.732 --> 00:43:30.233
[whines softly]

984
00:43:33.945 --> 00:43:35.196
I messed up.

985
00:43:35.280 --> 00:43:37.073
[whines]

986
00:43:37.157 --> 00:43:38.825
I have to own it.

987
00:43:40.243 --> 00:43:43.913
Hopefully. Shannon appreciates
the honesty and forgives me.

988
00:43:43.997 --> 00:43:44.956
[whines]

989
00:43:47.167 --> 00:43:49.169
[suspenseful music playing]

990
00:44:12.484 --> 00:44:14.736
Hey. Hey. have you seen Shannon?

991
00:44:14.819 --> 00:44:16.905
Um. she's not here.

992
00:44:16.988 --> 00:44:18.490
Something really bad happened.

993
00:44:18.573 --> 00:44:21.117
I know. I-I just need to talk to her.
It was a misunderstand--

994
00:44:21.201 --> 00:44:23.244
Shannon's mom
was in a car accident last night.

995
00:44:24.120 --> 00:44:25.246
In front of the school.

996
00:44:26.247 --> 00:44:27.791
She's dead.

997
00:44:28.875 --> 00:44:30.877
[somber. percussive music playing]

998
00:44:49.896 --> 00:44:51.898
♪ ♪

999
00:45:17.257 --> 00:45:19.259
♪ ♪

999
00:45:20.305 --> 00:46:20.170
Do you want subtitles for any video?
